It's just a mashup of Elton John songs with Dua singing the hook to Rocketman, Dua and Elton have no chemistry, and the move can be seen as cynical. But on the other hand, this sounds amazing. All I wanted out of this was Elton and Dua's awesomeness colliding with each other in a beautiful way, and that's exactly what I get. This is easily one of the best official mashups of an artist's work, right up there with The Click's Overture and Schmoyoho, Accent on the Yo by The Gregory Brothers. I get the hate, but Cold Heart is beautiful, and does exactly what it sets out to do. 8/10.
